   "source": [
    "# Interview Prep: 26 - The Technical Portfolio & Resume\n",
    "\n",
    "Getting the interview is the first step. For Senior and Staff roles, your resume must speak the language of **Business Impact** and **Technical Leadership**. This notebook covers how to market yourself to elite companies.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Writing for \"Impact\", not \"Features\"\n",
    "\n",
    "### **The Strategy**: The \"Google X-Y-Z\" Formula\n",
    "\"Accomplished [X] as measured by [Y], by doing [Z].\"\n",
    "\n",
    "| Bad (Feature-focused) | Good (Impact-focused) |\n",
    "| :--- | :--- |\n",
    "| \"I used Python to build a chatbot.\" | \"Reduced customer support tickets by **25%** by architecting an AI-driven Chatbot using Python and Pinecone Vector Search.\" |\n",
    "| \"I managed the database.\" | \"Achieved **zero downtime** during a 50TB database migration by implementing the parallel-change pattern.\" |\n",
    "| \"I worked with React.\" | \"Improved frontend Lighthouse performance scores from **60 to 95** by introducing code-splitting and server-side rendering.\" |\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. The Staff Engineer Resume Structure\n",
    "\n",
    "At this level, avoid listing every technology you have ever touched. Focus on **Scope**:\n",
    "1. **Core Competencies**: (e.g., Distributed Systems, Technical Strategy, Team Leadership).\n",
    "2. **Selected Impact**: 3-4 deep bullet points that show you can handle ambiguity and lead teams.\n",
    "3. **Evidence of Influence**: Mentioning RFCs, Architecture Guild memberships, or cross-company standards you set.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. The Digital Portfolio\n",
    "\n",
    "**What every Senior/Staff Engineer should have**:\n",
    "- **GitHub**: Not a graveyard of forks. Pin your 3 best projects. Each must have a professional `README` with an architectural diagram.\n",
    "- **Technical Blog**: Documentation that you can explain complex topics. Even 3-4 high-quality articles about trade-offs (e.g., \"Why we chose Postgres over MongoDB\") are enough.\n",
    "- **Case Studies**: Documents that detail a problem, your solution, and the final business result.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Interview Prep: The \"Story Bank\"\n",
    "\n",
    "Before the interview, prepare 5 stories using the **STAR** method (Situation, Task, Action, Result):\n",
    "1. **Conflict**: A time you disagreed with a peer's technical choice.\n",
    "2. **Failure**: A time you caused an outage or made a wrong decision.\n",
    "3. **Leadership**: A time you helped a team teammate grow without being their manager.\n",
    "4. **Complexity**: The most difficult technical bug you ever solved.\n",
    "5. **Business**: A time you prioritized the business needs over "perfect" code.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Coding Scenario: Estimating Your Worth\n",
    "\n",
    "**Task**: Calculate the ROI (Return on Investment) of a project you led to prove your impact in an interview.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_roi(dev_hours_saved_per_month, avg_hourly_rate):\n",
    "    # Annual value of the optimization\n",
    "    annual_savings = dev_hours_saved_per_month * 12 * avg_hourly_rate\n",
    "    return annual_savings\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scenario: You automated a manual CI/CD process, saving 5 hours/week for 20 devs.\n",
    "savings = calculate_roi(5 * 4 * 20, 80)\n",
    "print(f\"This automation project saved the company: ${savings:,} per year.\")\n",
    "print(\"Mentioning a number like this in an interview is a guaranteed way to stand out.\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
